fields.title: Bicycle Repair
fields.description: Come learn how to change a tire, tighten tension chords, and fix your brakes. Bring your bike and we will do some hands-on repairs at the shop!

fields.title: Cheap and Healthy Meal Prep
fields.description: We will be hosting a meal prep class at our lodge so we can support our canned food drive. The class will focus on quick, easy, and affordable meal prep work for busy people on a budget. Our veteran kitchen lead will be teaching you yummy meals that your kids will love! Free with the cost of one canned good per person. All ages welcome.

fields.title: Fix a Flat
fields.description: Edward, one of our long term volunteers, will be leading a class on how to change a flat tire. The class will cover the tools you need, where to buy them, and how to change a tire with variations for different abilities and vehicles. The event will be held in our back parking lot and is free to all ages.

fields.title: Learn Spanish: Beginner
fields.description: Spanish for beginners! Open to all.

fields.title: Garden Basics 101
fields.description: Join us in our community garden to learn the basics of vegetable gardening. Event will last two hours long. At the end, we will be giving out several varieties of tomato plants. Be sure to bring plenty of water and sunscreen. Gardening gloves and sturdy shoes are a plus.

fields.title: Free Tax Help
fields.description: H&R Block will be hosting a two hour event at the Shelby Park Community Center for tax help. Please bring all of your tax forms and receipts you may need. Mask required.

fields.title: Environmentally Safe Home Repair
fields.description: With so many new homeowners during the pandemic housing boom, Cook's wants to promote safe and environmentally friendly home repair. We will be going over different materials that are sturdy and safe, practices that are environmentally friendly, and providing a list of wholesalers.

fields.title: Easy Composting
fields.description: This kid friendly event will be going over many ways of easy composting! We will talk about why composting is important and how to build several different varieties of compost bins. Come with garden clothes on.
